article.description: William & Mary coast to a 31-7 win over Hampton
article.headline: William & Mary coast to a 31-7 win over Hampton
article.linkText: William & Mary coast to a 31-7 win over Hampton
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- Kendell Anderson rushed for 97 yards and two scores as William & Mary beat Hampton 31-7 on Saturday night. Mikal Abdul-Saboor had 111 yards and one touchdown, Keith McBride II added 63 and William & Mary (1-1) combined to run for 277 yards on 47 carries. Michael Graham was 9 of 21 for 106 yards for the Tribe. Coming off a narrow loss to West Virginia last week, William & Mary dominated from the start, pilling up 232 yards of total offense in the first half, compared to 46 for Hampton. Jaylian Williamson threw a 2-yard touchdown pass to Jorrian Washington for Hampton's lone score. The Pirates (0-2) were limited to 11 first downs and lost one fumble. Hampton is 0-4 all-time against the Tribe. The teams have not met since 2004.
